    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nBackslashes are valid characters in unix paths.\r\nCurrent implementation of `vim.fs.normalize` converts all backslashes to forward slashes, resulting in invalid/wrong paths.\r\n\r\nsee: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/27958#issuecomment-2022937067\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`:lua =vim.fs.normalize([[/a/b\\c]])` --> becomes `/a/b/c`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBackslashes should be untouched for unix paths.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2718+g1bfe6fdce\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim.fs\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux archlinux 6.7.5-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": "2024-03-29T16:23:02Z",
